contentrichtext.text: {{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} {{nihongo|'''Niisato'''|新里村|Niisato-mura}} was a [[villages of Japan|village]] located in [[Seta District, Gunma|Seta District]], [[Gunma Prefecture|Gunma]], [[Japan]]. On June 13, 2005 Niisato, along with the village of [[Kurohone, Gunma|Kurohone]], also from [[Seta District, Gunma|Seta District]], was merged into the expanded city of [[Kiryū, Gunma|Kiryū]]. [[Category:Dissolved municipalities of Gunma Prefecture]] {{Gunma-geo-stub}}
